to examine national approaches to the award of damages under the head of loss of housekeeping capacity, and to compare the levels of damages so awarded. The research will therefore address both the concepts employed in different national systems and, by means of practical case studies, the compensation actually paid in individual cases. The results of the research comprise ten country reports (Austria, England and Wales, France, Germany, Italy, The Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Spain and Switzerland) based on a Questionnaire (Part I: General Part and Doctrine, Part II: Concrete Assessment Examples) and a concluding Comparative Report.This project, "Loss of Housekeeping Capacity", was undertaken at the request of the Swiss Insurance Association.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aDamageszEurope. 0aHome economicszEurope. 0aPersonal injurieszEurope. 4aSchadensersatz /Rechtsvergleichung. 4aSchadensersatz. 7aLAW / Torts.2bisacsh  aComparative Law.  aCompensation.1 aAskeland, Bjarte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBargelli, Elena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEngelhard, Esther, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiesen, Ivo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGleixner, Elisabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aG’sell-Macrez, Florence, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarner, Ernst, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKarner, Ernst, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLandolt, Hardy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLudwichowska-Redo, Katarzyna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1